<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="834" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="125.[812,1405,1810,2235]" lastBlockId="125.[198,1403,2243,2906]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,1088,2046,2079]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body mean 184-2 mm (males) and 250-5 mm (females), tail mean 201-1 mm (males) and 199 mm (females); weight mean 135 g. The Lunda Rope Squirrel is medium-sized and has olive tinged dorsum, with small black spots and faint buff longitudinal stripe from shoulder to hips and buff eye ring. Venteris light gray, suffused with tan; tail is slightly longer than body and subtly ringed with dark black and gold.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="834" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="125.[198,1403,2243,2906]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,311,2361,2394]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">Habitat.</emphasis>
Might prefer forest-savanna mosaics, sandy woodlands, and lowto mediumelevation moist forests.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
