<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="834" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="125.[198,1403,2243,2906]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,547,2676,2709]" pageId="125" pageNumber="834">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Lunda Rope Squirrel is very poorly known, with little information available on its distribution, ecological requirements, and population size. Sightings have not been reported since the mid-1900s, and it is probably uncommon orrare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
